            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/1967-chevy-c10-cancer-survivor/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ".",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "quote",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "For many of these kids, the event was a welcome distraction from the stresses of everyday life. With ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "COVID-19 concerns",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/covid-19-survivor-saved/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " chief among their parents’ concerns, they’ve been cut off from school, friends, and many other outlets.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/09/Ferrari-Dealer-Gives-Child-Cancer-Patients-Free-Rides-2.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As many enthusiasts know, once you get into a car and drive for fun, many of your worries seem to melt away. That’s especially true if you’re in a fun vehicle ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "on a track",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/features-3/walt-disney-world-speedway/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " where you can just concentrate on being one with the machine, feeling it effortlessly eating up the blacktop as you find the perfect line through turns. It’s a soothing yet exhilarating sensation not easily replicated.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "To make the event possible, Ferrari of Atlanta has recruited the help of several car clubs and local law enforcement agencies. That meant no matter what a child’s interest, whether it’s Mopar muscle cars, a track-only race car, or a high-end European luxury sedan, they were able to experience it firsthand.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/09/Ferrari-Dealer-Gives-Child-Cancer-Patients-Free-Rides3.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Not only did the kids get to live the dream of riding around a track in many cool cars, the event generated about $100,000 to help child-centered charitable organizations like Camp Sunshine, Atlanta Ronald McDonald House Charities, and CURE Childhood Cancer. Sponsors helped with the fundraising, as did Ferrari customers. There was even a silent auction with several items featured, like a painting of God touching Adam’s finger, just like on the ceiling of the Sistine Chapel, only with a Ferrari F40 between the two. This proves yet again car people have heart and love to help out others in need, especially children.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
